WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:19.896 --> 00:22.148
I'm glad you decided
to come, Maggie-Sue.

00:22.315 --> 00:24.734
The road's a lonely place.

00:24.901 --> 00:27.028
And the wife
isn't much of a traveller.

00:28.154 --> 00:29.989
The wife isn't a lot of things.

00:42.752 --> 00:44.796
Oh, it's nothing to be
afraid of.

00:46.214 --> 00:48.675
It's just a part of
plain ol' everyday lovemaking.

00:49.676 --> 00:52.929
I remember when the president
said it wasn't even sex, really,

00:53.096 --> 00:54.889
more like a form of greeting,
a...

00:55.932 --> 00:57.892
..show of affection
between friends.

01:01.020 --> 01:02.939
Sonofabitch! Jesus! Fuck!

01:11.614 --> 01:14.117
Oh, fuck, oh, fuck,
oh, fuck, oh, fuck.

01:17.579 --> 01:20.165
Shit. Shit!

01:22.417 --> 01:24.753
It's OK.
D...d...don't try and move.

01:24.919 --> 01:27.005
I'm going to call for help.

01:30.258 --> 01:32.218
Ugh!

02:16.513 --> 02:18.306
Our Father,
who does art in heaven,

02:18.473 --> 02:20.517
deliver me from evil, with
liberty and justice for all...

02:39.327 --> 02:42.205
The idea is that
like attracts like.

02:42.372 --> 02:44.123
That's why it's called
the law of attraction.

02:44.290 --> 02:46.751
Just focus on...
focus on positive things

02:46.918 --> 02:49.420
and you'll end up
with positive results.

02:49.587 --> 02:53.258
Focus on the negative and you'll
end up with more of the same.

02:53.424 --> 02:58.012
My recent illness, for instance,
or this shithole I'm living in,

02:58.179 --> 03:01.015
direct manifestation
of negative thought.

03:01.182 --> 03:04.060
Thankfully, I've put
that awful disease behind me.

03:04.227 --> 03:08.189
Soon, this dreary dump
will be a thing of the past.

03:08.356 --> 03:11.442
But I am grateful for all of it.

03:11.609 --> 03:13.236
Wake-up calls, really,

03:13.403 --> 03:16.823
to get me to change
my doom-and-gloom outlook

03:16.990 --> 03:20.827
and step into the light
of my own joyous prosperity.

03:20.994 --> 03:23.496
That's the promise
I make myself.

03:37.260 --> 03:41.139
You of all people know I live up
to the promises I make.

03:54.903 --> 03:58.239
I want to thank you, Michael.

03:58.406 --> 04:00.033
Without your encouragement,

04:00.199 --> 04:02.076
Norman might never have shown
his true colours.

04:03.953 --> 04:08.958
A whining, pathetic man.
Angry and empty...

04:09.125 --> 04:13.963
Still, I drew his negativity
to me, I suppose.

04:15.298 --> 04:17.382
Law of attraction.
You see how it works, Michael?

04:17.550 --> 04:19.177
You willed bad things for me,

04:19.344 --> 04:22.055
but you only brought on
bad things for yourself.

04:23.681 --> 04:26.684
Just like that
little sister of yours.

04:26.851 --> 04:31.689
Oh, I have a house guest coming,
so it's time for you to go now.

04:32.690 --> 04:35.318
Bon voyage, as they say.

07:11.349 --> 07:14.560
Must've hurt like a motherfucker.

07:14.727 --> 07:16.521
For a second I thought
you really were dead.

07:16.687 --> 07:18.773
You have to commit
if you want to sell it.

07:18.940 --> 07:20.775
You've got some giant balls
taking a hit like that.

07:20.942 --> 07:23.986
The Rumanceks are world-renowned
for their testicular girth.

07:29.575 --> 07:31.202
A thousand thankyous
for what you did.

07:31.369 --> 07:33.287
Yeah, well, you saved my life.

07:34.455 --> 07:37.625
Anyways, it was great being out
with you guys - full moon.

07:37.792 --> 07:39.418
It felt good.

07:39.585 --> 07:41.212
- As well it should.
- Alright, cheers, boys.

07:43.131 --> 07:45.591
- These are your people.
You're one of us. -Cheers.

07:45.758 --> 07:47.343
Seeing as how this worked out
so well,

07:47.510 --> 07:49.095
I've got something else
in the pipeline that...

07:49.262 --> 07:51.055
No. I can't.

07:56.894 --> 07:58.688
Miranda and Nadia
are still out there.

07:59.689 --> 08:02.817
Understood. Don't mean to push.
I totally get it.

08:05.903 --> 08:08.281
You're sure that no cops
are gonna look for this truck?

08:08.447 --> 08:10.908
Not in a million years.

08:12.076 --> 08:14.912
That is the beauty
of thieving from thieves.

08:16.539 --> 08:20.835
50 crates
at 200 pounds per.

08:21.002 --> 08:23.296
Flip it cheap to move it fast.

08:23.462 --> 08:26.215
So, conservatively,

08:26.382 --> 08:29.510
we're looking at right around

08:29.677 --> 08:31.888
1.2 million and change.

08:32.054 --> 08:35.183
You fellas did good.

08:35.349 --> 08:37.434
Well, he was the brains
behind the whole thing.

08:37.602 --> 08:39.395
But you, Peter,
were a rock star.

08:39.562 --> 08:42.273
I'll store it here
while you work a deal.

08:42.440 --> 08:44.066
You're reaching out
to our regular buyers?

08:44.232 --> 08:45.943
I've got it handled.

08:50.406 --> 08:53.201
- Did you see her?
- Briefly.

08:54.535 --> 08:57.705
I try to talk to her
as often as I can, but...

08:59.415 --> 09:01.042
..she moves around so much.

09:01.209 --> 09:03.211
Sometimes I think
things are harder for her

09:03.377 --> 09:05.213
over in the old country
than she lets on.

09:06.464 --> 09:09.342
- How did she look?
- Peter, listen to me.

09:09.508 --> 09:11.135
Your mother is well.

09:11.302 --> 09:14.513
She misses you,
but she's surrounded by family -

09:14.680 --> 09:16.307
people who love her too.

09:16.474 --> 09:19.769
She told me to give you this.
Said you were expecting it.

09:19.936 --> 09:21.395
Mmm.

09:23.814 --> 09:25.608
This belonged to my grandmother.

09:27.401 --> 09:29.862
Thank you. I know you went to
a lot of trouble.

09:30.029 --> 09:33.950
Trouble
is what our people live for.

09:38.371 --> 09:40.248
You...you OK, bro?

09:40.414 --> 09:42.208
Yeah.

09:47.964 --> 09:49.715
Lynda approves.

09:50.841 --> 09:52.635
And so do I.

09:54.095 --> 09:56.347
Now you have permission
to ask my cousin to marry you.

09:58.099 --> 10:00.017
OK.

10:07.108 --> 10:08.776
I will make her a queen.

10:08.943 --> 10:12.029
You better treat her right
or I'll fucking kill you.

10:13.030 --> 10:15.032
- Welcome to the family.
- Oh.

10:30.006 --> 10:31.924
I'm getting...

10:33.342 --> 10:35.136
..absolutely nothing.

10:38.222 --> 10:40.099
All we can do is keep trying.

10:41.309 --> 10:43.686
I had a case
out in LA once.

10:43.853 --> 10:46.147
Wife went missing,
suspected homicide,

10:46.314 --> 10:48.357
and the family brought in
a clairvoyant.

10:49.358 --> 10:53.404
Never did find the woman, but,
man, I tell you that psychic -

10:53.571 --> 10:55.573
mad skills
locating the client's wallet.

10:55.740 --> 10:57.742
Mm-hm.

10:59.827 --> 11:03.205
I have a special gift
for divining assholes.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.751
Far be it for me
to cast aspersions,

11:06.917 --> 11:09.462
but when you're trafficking
in the realm of the unseen,

11:09.628 --> 11:11.297
there are those who might want
to take advantage -

11:11.464 --> 11:13.966
grifters and so forth.

11:15.009 --> 11:17.178
Present company excepted,
of course.

11:20.014 --> 11:23.059
- I gotta go.
- Alright. Thanks, Dee.

11:23.225 --> 11:24.727
Mm-hm.

11:27.646 --> 11:31.609
OK, smart guy, what do you got?

11:31.776 --> 11:33.527
Transcripts of my interviews

11:33.694 --> 11:36.739
with every patient
in Spivak's practice.

11:36.906 --> 11:39.075
Unremarkable for
anything out of the ordinary.

11:39.241 --> 11:42.286
Travelled the world a little bit
doing pro bono medical stuff.

11:42.453 --> 11:44.372
Was not banging his nurse.

11:44.538 --> 11:46.582
A better man than I am.
Real dime piece.

11:46.749 --> 11:48.376
What else?

11:48.542 --> 11:50.711
Spivak got his medical degree
at Leipzig University

11:50.878 --> 11:53.297
in Germany, studied immunology
at the University of Maine...

11:53.464 --> 11:55.091
- He's German?
- Beats me.

11:55.257 --> 11:57.426
I traced him as far back
as med school. Dead-ends there.

11:57.593 --> 12:00.888
- What about Miranda's family?
- Father is deceased.

12:01.055 --> 12:02.890
Tracked down the mother
in Provo, Utah.

12:03.057 --> 12:04.975
Hadn't spoken to her daughter
in 10 years.

12:05.142 --> 12:06.769
Contacted every morgue
and hospital

12:06.936 --> 12:08.562
up and down the east coast.

12:08.729 --> 12:11.565
No Jane Does matching the
description. Same with the baby.

12:11.732 --> 12:13.234
Basically, you show up
empty-handed

12:13.401 --> 12:14.652
expecting to get paid.

12:14.819 --> 12:18.114
I put in the hours, I get paid.
That's how it works.

12:18.280 --> 12:20.908
Sounds like a grift to me.

12:21.075 --> 12:23.035
Hmm.

12:23.202 --> 12:26.455
You care so much about these
folks, gotta ask, why me?

12:26.622 --> 12:28.416
Why not go to the police?

12:29.708 --> 12:32.294
Police get involved,
things get public.

12:32.461 --> 12:35.589
And you're looking to be
discreet. I understand.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.383
But this baby you got me
searching for,

12:37.550 --> 12:39.218
there's no birth certificate.

12:39.385 --> 12:41.554
Technically speaking,
it hasn't been born.

12:41.720 --> 12:43.931
People hire me to find shit out,
mostly where's the money,

12:44.098 --> 12:45.724
who's fucking who, so forth.

12:45.891 --> 12:48.477
What is it that you're not
telling me about this kid?

12:48.644 --> 12:50.271
This girl?

12:50.438 --> 12:53.357
I gotta know.
Otherwise I can't do my job.

12:55.067 --> 12:58.654
This is
all the information you need.

13:01.699 --> 13:04.243
Keep digging on Spivak.
I expect results.

13:17.214 --> 13:19.508
Dr Pryce.

13:21.427 --> 13:24.013
- There's an anomaly.
- Anomaly tells me nothing.

13:24.180 --> 13:25.806
But it would be an anomaly,
I suppose,

13:25.973 --> 13:27.808
if you actually communicated
meaningful information.

13:27.975 --> 13:31.020
The specimen is experiencing
an excessive amount

13:31.187 --> 13:33.189
of chromosomal deletion,
which is causing it to...

13:33.355 --> 13:36.525
I know what it causes.
Did you try the...the...

13:37.860 --> 13:40.404
Blinsky, you know what I asked
you to do, the amniotic...

13:40.571 --> 13:42.198
..the...the...the thing,
you know.

13:42.364 --> 13:44.867
It had no effect.

13:45.034 --> 13:46.660
Did you get any sleep
last night?

13:46.827 --> 13:49.079
That's no concern of yours.

13:49.246 --> 13:50.915
How did this happen?

13:51.081 --> 13:54.835
I suspended the safety
protocols, as you asked,

13:55.002 --> 13:56.629
but the amount of growth hormone
required...

13:56.795 --> 14:01.091
Creeping mother of Jesus!
What are you trying to say?

14:02.092 --> 14:04.428
We should dispose of
the specimen and start over.

14:04.595 --> 14:07.306
Give up, in other words.

14:07.473 --> 14:09.808
I promoted you because I thought
you were a problem solver

14:09.975 --> 14:11.644
and it turns out
you're just a gutless quitter.

14:11.810 --> 14:14.146
- Dr Pryce...
- What?!

14:14.313 --> 14:16.315
..your meeting started
20 minutes ago.

14:16.482 --> 14:18.901
My meeting? Wh...what meeting?

14:19.068 --> 14:21.529
The one I reminded you about
an hour ago.

14:23.322 --> 14:26.700
Right. Fix it.

14:30.246 --> 14:32.831
We need to make this jury
understand

14:32.998 --> 14:35.042
that there's absolutely
no correlation

14:35.209 --> 14:36.835
between our product

14:37.002 --> 14:40.381
and the deaths caused by liver
failure their lawsuit alleges.

14:40.548 --> 14:42.675
Apologies. Urgent matter.

14:43.842 --> 14:45.344
Continue.

14:46.345 --> 14:49.682
To do that, we need to take
a long, hard look

14:49.848 --> 14:52.309
at who these so-called
victims actually are.

14:52.476 --> 14:54.311
You look like shit.

14:54.478 --> 14:56.146
You've inherited
your mother's charm.

14:56.313 --> 14:57.940
Fuck you.
What have you found out?

14:58.107 --> 15:00.776
- We're in the process. -I assume
that's code for nothing.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.570
You promised me
you'd have answers.

15:02.736 --> 15:05.155
And I will. It just takes
a little patience.

15:05.322 --> 15:07.283
Gentlemen,

15:07.449 --> 15:10.869
if there's anything
that you don't understand,

15:11.036 --> 15:12.788
perhaps you've missed,
I can help you through...

15:12.955 --> 15:15.082
Spare me the hand job, Gans.

15:15.249 --> 15:17.209
This poor people's march
will save the company 100 mil,

15:17.376 --> 15:19.211
well and good, but I...

15:21.880 --> 15:23.716
I...

15:26.093 --> 15:28.137
That is to say, I...

15:28.304 --> 15:29.930
Get out.

15:30.097 --> 15:33.392
I said, "Get out."
Go. Leave us alone.

15:42.526 --> 15:45.446
You really need to dial back on
the caffeine there, buddy boy.

15:45.613 --> 15:47.239
I'm nearly done
mapping the genome

15:47.406 --> 15:49.116
from the skin sample we found
in Spivak's office.

15:49.283 --> 15:51.368
How long does it take?
It's been six weeks.

15:51.535 --> 15:54.121
- I thought you were a fucking genius.
- I am a fucking genius.

15:54.288 --> 15:55.956
It took 13 years to map
the human genome.

15:56.123 --> 15:58.375
- And I'm getting close...
- I want my kid back.

16:00.294 --> 16:02.796
- Roman, I'm trying to help you.
- I know.

16:07.009 --> 16:08.636
I'm almost out of nutrient.

16:08.802 --> 16:11.889
There'll be a new batch ready
this afternoon.

16:12.056 --> 16:13.682
I have to get your sister ready.

16:13.849 --> 16:16.977
I swear, if this fucking hearing
goes sideways, I'm gonna...

16:19.188 --> 16:20.981
We have to let this play out.

16:28.656 --> 16:30.491
I hate lorazepam.

16:30.658 --> 16:35.037
Makes me feel like my brain's
made out of chewing gum.

16:35.204 --> 16:37.456
It will help you relax.

16:44.421 --> 16:46.256
There we go.

16:47.341 --> 16:49.134
Big day today.

16:51.011 --> 16:52.930
It's really been six weeks?

16:53.097 --> 16:54.807
That's the nature
of psychotic departures.

16:54.973 --> 16:57.184
You were overwhelmed
by traumatic events,

16:57.351 --> 16:59.186
your mind disconnected.

17:00.479 --> 17:02.314
I was afraid
you wouldn't come back.

17:03.524 --> 17:06.484
The last thing I remember
was Prycilla.

17:08.319 --> 17:11.156
So much blood.

17:12.741 --> 17:16.537
When that picture comes
in your mind, turn the channel

17:16.704 --> 17:19.248
until you find
something far less painful.

17:20.374 --> 17:22.334
The meds will help you do that.

17:23.377 --> 17:25.421
What did you do with her body?

17:25.587 --> 17:28.424
Shelley, it's better
if you don't...

17:28.590 --> 17:30.426
Tell me.

17:32.219 --> 17:34.388
She was laid to rest.

17:34.555 --> 17:37.182
Under a beautiful oak
overlooking the river.

17:37.349 --> 17:39.518
My reading tree.

17:44.273 --> 17:47.443
Do I have to go back
to live with her?

17:48.694 --> 17:51.989
Roman is doing his best
to see that that doesn't happen.

17:54.032 --> 17:56.076
Can't I just stay here?

17:56.243 --> 17:57.870
Nothing would make me happier,

17:58.036 --> 17:59.872
but the courts
would never allow it.

18:00.038 --> 18:02.541
- I'm afraid, Uncle Johann.
- No. Don't be.

18:03.834 --> 18:07.129
Your brother and I will be
with you every step of the way,

18:07.296 --> 18:09.423
whatever happens.

18:09.590 --> 18:13.260
And these will help you
keep those fears in check.

18:16.764 --> 18:18.390
It's my understanding

18:18.557 --> 18:20.225
that due to the lack
of credible evidence,

18:20.392 --> 18:22.853
the people wish to drop
all charges against Ms Godfrey?

18:23.020 --> 18:26.190
- We do, Your Honour.
- So ordered.

18:27.232 --> 18:30.319
And as to the challenge
of guardianship

18:30.486 --> 18:32.404
filed by Roman Godfrey,

18:32.571 --> 18:35.324
the court has found it
without merit.

18:37.159 --> 18:39.077
Young lady, would you
approach the bench, please?

18:45.375 --> 18:48.045
Ms Godfrey, I'm releasing you
into your mother's care.

18:51.673 --> 18:53.509
Do you understand
what I'm telling you?

18:54.802 --> 18:56.428
Yes, ma'am.

18:56.595 --> 18:59.765
I should warn you that
even a legal finding of fact

18:59.932 --> 19:01.642
won't make your troubles
disappear.

19:01.809 --> 19:04.019
And due to the notoriety
of this case,

19:04.186 --> 19:06.605
there may be individuals
who harbour anger towards you.

19:06.772 --> 19:09.942
However misguided, it is real
and potentially dangerous.

19:10.108 --> 19:13.445
I wish you the best of luck.
You're free to go.

19:13.612 --> 19:17.699
- Thank you. Come on, sweety.
- We need to talk. Now.

19:23.121 --> 19:25.207
Don't think I don't know
what your act is all about.

19:25.374 --> 19:27.626
You can't wait to get
your hands on her trust fund.

19:27.793 --> 19:29.628
Oh, Roman, this negativity,
it's not good for your health...

19:29.795 --> 19:31.630
How long do you think
she's gonna stay with you

19:31.797 --> 19:33.423
when she finds out
you murdered Norman, huh?

19:33.590 --> 19:35.259
I have no idea
what you're talking about...

19:35.425 --> 19:38.220
- Fuck you!
- Roman, calm down.

19:38.387 --> 19:40.013
Your sister's mental state
is extremely fragile.

19:40.180 --> 19:42.474
Any trauma could induce
a severe conversion reaction.

19:42.641 --> 19:44.309
What does that even mean?

19:44.476 --> 19:47.354
If she goes over the edge again,
we may never get her back.

19:55.112 --> 19:57.322
I missed you so much.

20:01.994 --> 20:04.496
You know I love you, right?

20:04.663 --> 20:07.749
She's not your jailer
and this isn't forever.

20:09.084 --> 20:12.713
I'm only a phone call away.
I'll make this right, I promise.

20:12.880 --> 20:14.673
Let's go home.

20:59.885 --> 21:01.678
Animal!

21:04.598 --> 21:06.433
Pay no attention.

21:13.273 --> 21:16.526
Do we come clean and tell
this Sherlock homeboy what's up?

21:16.693 --> 21:19.446
You mean, that our missing baby
with telekinetic powers

21:19.613 --> 21:22.574
was taken by a flying reptoid
with a 30-foot wingspan

21:22.741 --> 21:24.701
who had been masquerading around
town as the family doctor?

21:24.868 --> 21:26.703
Or do we start slow
and whisper in his ear

21:26.870 --> 21:28.538
that he's been living in a world

21:28.705 --> 21:31.541
of upirs and vargulfs the whole
time and he didn't even know it?

21:31.708 --> 21:33.335
Oh, but I'd leave out
the spontaneous freak lactation.

21:33.502 --> 21:35.128
That's too unbelievable.

21:35.295 --> 21:37.965
Even if we're just spinning
our wheels with this guy,

21:38.131 --> 21:39.925
we can't just not do anything.

21:44.388 --> 21:47.599
What if we never find them?
What if they're dead?

21:47.766 --> 21:50.978
Don't go there.
We can't think like that.

21:52.312 --> 21:53.939
I'm sorry.

21:54.106 --> 21:55.774
Tell me some good news.

21:58.360 --> 22:00.445
Destiny and Andreas
are getting hitched.

22:03.156 --> 22:05.784
- Shit.
- Shit.

22:05.951 --> 22:07.744
Feels right.

22:10.497 --> 22:12.791
Do you mind if I crash
at your place for a while?

22:12.958 --> 22:16.169
- Give the lovebirds some space?
- Mi casa and shit.

22:39.151 --> 22:40.777
Don't wait around for me.

23:00.255 --> 23:02.049
Hey.

23:57.270 --> 24:01.608
It's not Versailles,
but it's clean...relatively.

24:01.775 --> 24:03.401
And it's temporary.

24:03.568 --> 24:05.487
We need to get you
one of those pill organisers

24:05.654 --> 24:07.280
with the days of the week on it.

24:07.447 --> 24:11.910
It doesn't matter where we stay.
It's just a place to sleep.

24:13.036 --> 24:14.955
Oh, that's very understanding
of you, dear,

24:15.122 --> 24:17.499
but once we get our finances
sorted out,

24:17.666 --> 24:19.918
we'll find the perfect spot
where we can be comfortable,

24:20.085 --> 24:21.878
just like before.

24:23.255 --> 24:26.216
And this one
is to help you sleep.

24:26.383 --> 24:28.009
Makes me dizzy.

24:28.176 --> 24:30.804
Oh, you can't be dizzy
when you're asleep.

